Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.56,0:00:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.19,0:00:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was the basis for the ruling the judge made \N regarding the events in Stuttgart in 1986
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.16,0:00:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my.  Silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.33,0:00:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this some sort of Oriental Zen temple or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Eimer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.62,0:00:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to hear your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.21,0:00:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that is, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.92,0:00:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, can anyone break this silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.27,0:00:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the criminally late has decided to show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.40,0:00:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're thirteen minutes late today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.53,0:00:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears your part time pizza delivery \N job was especially busy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.24,0:01:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Professor Kronecker.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.58,0:01:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.91,0:01:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you take your seat, let me ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have enough stamina left to analyze...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.96,0:01:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the basis for the judge's ruling \N on the events of Stuttgart in 1986?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.92,0:01:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.86,0:01:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.69,0:01:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.17,0:01:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the defendant claimed that the \N kidnapping was the objective...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.97,0:01:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the death of the victim was accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.22,0:01:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After carefully examining the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.81,0:01:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it was concluded that the murder was indeed accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.37,0:01:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, because the murder was a crime of passion...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.52,0:01:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I believe the murderer was merely \N sentenced to fifteen years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.20,0:01:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.53,0:01:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and take your seat, Ms. Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:22.97,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(113,90)\pos(367,337)}Heidelberg, \N Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.61,0:03:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to you, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If nobody had said anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.89,0:03:28.72,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,133)\pos(358,319)}The Girl From Heidelberg
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.37,0:03:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that demon Kronecker would have \N assigned another fifty page essay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifty pages may be underestimating him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.92,0:03:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should treat Nina for saving our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.25,0:03:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about today, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the two of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.51,0:03:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:44.20,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(284,0)\pos(355,364)}Nina Fortner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go to my club.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.14,0:03:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.60,0:03:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were rejected again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.89,0:03:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times does that make now, Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.64,0:03:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.02,0:03:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to meet the man who can catch Nina
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.37,0:04:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.00,0:04:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The boss is really gonna yell at me again if I'm late on the delivery!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.77,0:04:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.39,0:04:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The neighbors can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.36,0:04:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think you're too old to be saying things like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.19,0:04:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go wash your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.45,0:04:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  Did you dye your hair, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it look good?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.53,0:04:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you have to dye it blond at your age?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.50,0:04:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that, Dad.  It suits her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.54,0:04:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like she's in a costume parade or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:05:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you like how Mom always looks so young?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, speaking of costume parades...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.55,0:05:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the children were all dressed up in costumes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.35,0:05:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that must be for St. Adrian's costume parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to dress up like that when I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.69,0:05:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did dress up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.20,0:05:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, yeah.  That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was around here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.16,0:05:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.34,0:05:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.59,0:05:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You made such a big fuss, since you were so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.92,0:05:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.05,0:05:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A costume parade, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.57,0:06:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The distant spring."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.91,0:06:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am tired of waiting for the spring that will never come."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.12,0:06:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.41,0:06:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanna should just get over her breakup already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.75,0:06:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I will give you the world's most beautiful flower."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.55,0:06:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was born to bury you with flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!  I wonder who sent that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.94,0:06:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty slick, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.98,0:06:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How have you been feeling, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.73,0:06:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing really great thanks to you, Dr. Geitel!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.11,0:06:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I saw you were in a good mood from the look \N on your face when you entered the counseling room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.20,0:06:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've stopped having that dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The dream where a monster rises out of the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.09,0:07:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.17,0:07:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, I've been sleeping so soundly that \N I haven't even had time to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why I was haunted by that dream everyday...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody becomes insecure during \N their time as a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.87,0:07:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One's dreams and anxieties about \N the future mix together...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and one's identity becomes lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can spend a lifetime searching, but \N you'll never know who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do our best to live for the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.43,0:07:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...while trying to look for the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.49,0:07:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!  I'm doing my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dream is to become a prosecutor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.66,0:07:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.21,0:07:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's end our counseling session here for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.96,0:07:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.09,0:07:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina Fortner...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:07:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's such a bright girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.01,0:08:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't shake the feeling that her brightness is only \N an indication that she's running away from something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.29,0:08:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From a great darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.23,0:08:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.28,0:08:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "what"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playing dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.82,0:08:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.99,0:08:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was born to bury you with flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.70,0:08:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought you had the talent to write such poetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.29,0:08:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those words wouldn't come out of me even \N if you flipped me upside down and shook.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.92,0:08:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only given my email address to friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.22,0:08:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.68,0:08:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.93,0:08:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I know is that another rival has \N appeared in pursuit of my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.27,0:08:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the bizarre murder case in München...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.90,0:08:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the perpetrator, after first shooting \N the parents with a gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...strangled the two children to death with a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...can you give us an analysis on the judge's \N ruling from the trial records...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.21,0:09:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Ms. Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.26,0:09:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not understand my question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.88,0:09:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, the focus of the trial was the verdict...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the massacre..
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.35,0:09:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the... entire family...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.61,0:09:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the... evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.98,0:09:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the... evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.53,0:09:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even you can't answer a question sometimes, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.75,0:09:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.54,0:09:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.92,0:09:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.25,0:09:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.71,0:09:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to go to the infirmary?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:09:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.34,0:10:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just felt a little sick, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly felt dizzy... after hearing \N what the professor said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.85,0:10:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the family massacre case?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.98,0:10:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.65,0:10:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I thought you were pretty strong, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.11,0:10:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you turned out to be kind of delicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.78,0:10:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you watch a really scary movie \N when you were little or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet that counselor of yours would say something like...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you trace it back to its roots, it is nothing big."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Now, try to remember your childhood."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.00,0:10:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.09,0:10:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...don't have any memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.59,0:10:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any memories from before I was ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.82,0:11:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of my childhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.45,0:11:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:21.07,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,0)\pos(349,314)}Köln, \N Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.63,0:11:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.63,0:11:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both parents were really nice people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe they were killed like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.35,0:11:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.23,0:11:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, they did have a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.98,0:11:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think his name was Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.06,0:11:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He lived with them for about two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.57,0:11:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.44,0:11:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there such a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.45,0:11:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.99,0:11:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think his name was Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.49,0:11:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was about fourteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.62,0:11:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.37,0:11:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think there was a boy by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.29,0:11:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with the police or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.79,0:11:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Michael Reichmann.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.67,0:12:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was indeed in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.67,0:12:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't a very impressionable child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.05,0:12:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm embarrassed to say this, but \N I don't remember him very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.10,0:12:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if he had any friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.85,0:12:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, we don't have any records of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, there was a fire six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that a child named Michael...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.78,0:12:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did actually live in Köln until six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.66,0:12:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Michael's real name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.58,0:12:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.50,0:12:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there were times when I was called by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.46,0:12:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.30,0:12:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... what good does knowing that do for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.18,0:12:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I knew, he's still the elder of \N the twins, and a mass murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.10,0:12:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.44,0:13:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twins?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.82,0:13:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's his sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.53,0:13:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the younger sister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.15,0:13:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm coming to pick you up soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.41,0:13:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming to pick me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.57,0:13:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. There was one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.90,0:13:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was about seven or eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. and Mrs. Heinau were raising a \N boy before they were killed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.04,0:13:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of child was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.67,0:13:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.67,0:13:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.67,0:13:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they lived together for only about a year or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.26,0:13:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he have a younger sister with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.10,0:13:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.64,0:13:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I just want to forget about \N the incident with that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.39,0:13:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I almost moved away because of it back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.16,0:14:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know about that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.45,0:14:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you come up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.89,0:14:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to make some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.71,0:14:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.59,0:14:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.84,0:14:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.76,0:14:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.20,0:14:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.08,0:14:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.47,0:15:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a doctor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it from that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.85,0:15:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Dr. Tenma, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.58,0:15:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is coming to pick you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.44,0:15:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.56,0:15:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.77,0:15:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone sent me an anonymous email.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.19,0:15:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.03,0:15:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're not hoping for a prince on \N a white horse to come pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.53,0:15:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.87,0:15:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's got her head in the clouds again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.89,0:15:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was born to buy you with flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think anybody wrote like that nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.80,0:15:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, speaking of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.17,0:15:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's been a new guy sitting in our lectures lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.26,0:15:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sits in the legendary seat in room 12 where \N the professor will definitely call on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.02,0:15:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, the professor never calls on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.35,0:15:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right.  And do you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been staring at you the whole time, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.19,0:15:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.74,0:16:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's your prince on the white horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.91,0:16:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was very grateful to you, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said you saved his life, and were therefore \N more important than his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he call himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.34,0:16:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.76,0:16:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he said that wasn't his real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.64,0:16:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He opened his heart so much that he even told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.81,0:16:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just appeared out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.94,0:16:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was raised for about a year by the Heinau couple, who \N didn't have any children, in the place across from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.32,0:16:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, to be more precise...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.82,0:16:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was fourteen months, from March \N of 1987 to April of 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:16:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then one day, he suddenly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:17:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was an extremely smart child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.75,0:17:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was also very polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.24,0:17:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came to this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.93,0:17:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.51,0:17:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I live alone, I always welcomed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.35,0:17:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to sit in that chair...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.35,0:17:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and just continued with his studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.27,0:17:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He quickly mastered the English \N and French that I taught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.73,0:17:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was able to speak both languages \N fluently by the time he disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.90,0:17:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he was only twelve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.78,0:17:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you recall anything else about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.00,0:17:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He diligently listened to everything I had to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.62,0:17:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What type of stories do you think he \N showed the greatest interest in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.13,0:17:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stories of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.30,0:17:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,War?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.84,0:17:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In World War II...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.47,0:17:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I served on a U Boat in the navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.27,0:17:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The story he wanted to hear the most...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:18:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was the one about the time when we \N were attacked by an Allied destroyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.36,0:18:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traveling at 120 meters below the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.55,0:18:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...after being attacked by the enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.99,0:18:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we still continued to dive deeper \N after sustaining critical damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Within the ship, under pressure by \N the water, we endured our fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.70,0:18:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty-eight hours later, we returned from that living hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.34,0:18:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any normal child...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.25,0:18:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...would have enjoyed this story as an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.84,0:18:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.78,0:18:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he showed the most interest in...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.02,0:18:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ultimate fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.27,0:18:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They kind of reactions people have when \N they are on the brink of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was all he was interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.90,0:18:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was toying with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.78,0:18:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.37,0:18:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of expression did he have \N while he listened to your story?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:19:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably had sparkling eyes and a grin on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.58,0:19:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.04,0:19:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.34,0:19:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.63,0:19:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know that child's real name, \N nor do I know what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that he opened his heart \N to me earlier, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.19,0:19:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He will never open his heart to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.31,0:19:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one person he truly opened his heart to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.11,0:19:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that is his younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.44,0:19:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'm looking for that girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.82,0:19:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was going to get her when she turned twenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.37,0:19:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heidelberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.08,0:19:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful on your bike!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.76,0:19:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, I'm going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.32,0:19:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.  Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.97,0:19:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.11,0:20:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.57,0:20:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.61,0:20:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We decided, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.32,0:20:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That we'd tell her on her twentieth birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.74,0:20:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That she isn't our daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, I don't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.05,0:20:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?  You \N said you wanted to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.67,0:20:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We talked him into meeting you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.97,0:20:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you do well with your prince on his white horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.78,0:20:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.74,0:20:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Clara!  Baerde!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.81,0:20:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they do this without asking me first?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here he comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.71,0:21:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello, are you Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.59,0:21:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, I'm Otto Huberman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.78,0:21:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.95,0:21:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.70,0:21:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.70,0:21:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where have... I seen him before?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.72,0:21:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.34,0:22:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.99,0:22:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.78,0:22:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.24,0:22:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?  Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.62,0:22:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.68,0:22:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.28,0:22:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.41,0:22:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.54,0:22:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina, are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.70,0:22:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
